main event: John Doe observed several unidentified bright objects in the sky over Champaign, Illinois on June 6, 1960.
interesting points: The witness described the objects as round and hovering at a high altitude., The objects performed unusual aerial maneuvers and were visible for several minutes., The witness took several photographs of the objects which were included in the report., The initial reports of the sighting came from local law enforcement and civilian witnesses., The case remains unresolved with no definitive explanation for the sighting.
sighted object: multiple unidentified bright objects in the sky
witness description: John Doe considered a reliable and trustworthy witness.
